memoryAvailableBytes.name: memoryAvailableBytes
memoryAvailableBytes.description: Available Bytes displays the size of the virtual memory currently on the Zeroed, Free, and Standby lists. Zeroed and Free memory is ready for use, with Zeroed memory cleared to zeros. Standby memory is memory removed from a process's Working Set but still available. Notice that this is an instantaneous count, not an average over the time interval.

memoryCommitLimit.name: memoryCommitLimit
memoryCommitLimit.description: Commit Limit is the size (in bytes) of virtual memory that can be committed without having to extend the paging file(s). If the paging file(s) can be extended, this is a soft limit.

memoryCommittedBytes.name: memoryCommittedBytes
memoryCommittedBytes.description: Committed Bytes displays the size of virtual memory (in bytes) that has been Committed (as opposed to simply reserved). Committed memory must have backing (i.e., disk) storage available, or must be assured never to need disk storage (because main memory is large enough to hold it.) Notice that this is an instantaneous count, not an average over the time interval.

osProcUtil1.name: osProcUtil1
osProcUtil1.description: System Utilization over the last minute.

svrInfoTotalPhysicalRam.name: svrInfoTotalPhysicalRam
svrInfoTotalPhysicalRam.description: The amount of physical RAM in bytes.
